      "amount": "1/2 cup",
      "notes": "dairy or non-dairy alternative"
    },
    {
      "name": "fresh cilantro",
      "amount": "1/4 cup",
      "notes": "chopped, for garnish"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat 2 tbsp of oil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "Add the tadka spice blend and cook for 1 min.",
    "Add the red onion and cook until softened, about 5 min.",
    "Add the carrots, celery, and butternut squash, and cook for 5 min.",
    "Pour in the red wine and vegetable broth, and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 20 min.",
    "Stir in the garam masala, salt, and lemon juice.",
    "Add the heavy cream and stir until heated through.",
    "Taste and adjust the seasoning as needed.",
    "Garnish with chopped cilantro and serve hot."
  ],
